                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1426" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT KENDREW</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker. On the morning of the 9th of Aug., the prisoner pawned this painting for 30<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—on the Saturday following I saw an account in the paper that the painting was stolen—I sent to the prosecutor who identified it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> The master said he did not think it was me—they took me to the station, found the duplicate on me, and then the master swore I was the person, and this witness came the next day and swore I was the man. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> A man brought the prisoner to the shop—he doubled his fist at him and threatened him—I desired him to take him to the station, and tickets were found on him which correspond with the name he gave me, George Lovell.</p>
